hat uncovers the public and cultural dimensions of this always-controversial domain of private law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPersonal injurieszUnited States. 0aRace discriminationxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aSex discriminationxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aTortszUnited States. 7aLAW / Torts.2bisacsh  a911.  aChamallas.  aCompensation.  aCrow.  aDrawing.  aFund.  aInjury.  aJennifer.  aMartha.  aMeasure.  aSouth.  aVictim.  aWriggins.  aanalysis.  aanything.  aauthors.  abased.  abeen.  abiases.  acase.  ademonstrate.  adisparate.  aforms.  afrom.  agender.  ahave.  ain-depth.  aminorities.  aneutral.  apatterns.  aperpetuate.  aprove.  arace.  aranging.  arecovery.  aresurfaced.  athat.  atort.  atraditional.  aunder-compensated.  aupdated.  awomen.1 aWriggins, Jennifer B., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814790069423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814790069.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK